      "author": "UFAI (Adam)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>In automations, you can make an automation that will trigger if it change from “X” to “Anything”<br />\n</p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/a/1/a12df98f9f7187c58ba9ef887bb6a4b37bd757d6.png\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/optimized/3X/a/1/a12df98f9f7187c58ba9ef887bb6a4b37bd757d6_2_689x270.png\" alt=\"image\" width=\"689\" height=\"270\" /><div class=\"meta\"><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">1240×487 27.9 KB</span></div></a></div><p></p>\n<p>Workflows do not have this “Anything” status, even though it’s the same as a board automation.<br />\n</p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/3/d/3d4be3bee645113e4b9f9a3c9fad508141827d36.png\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/optimized/3X/3/d/3d4be3bee645113e4b9f9a3c9fad508141827d36_2_690x470.png\" alt=\"image\" width=\"690\" height=\"470\" /><div class=\"meta\"><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">1079×736 39.5 KB</span></div></a></div><p></p>\n<p>It’s very helpful because it future proofs the board. If we create a new status, I’d have to find every workflow that calls for technical call to anything and ensure the new status is put on them. It seems small, but adds up.</p>"
